@node Main "TiltOtix - Documentation"

                             'TiltOtix' 1.01

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'TiltOtix' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} where you have to move a coloured
bar from the upper left, to the lower right of the game board. The
game board is filled with 24 bars (the coloured bar and 23 'bow tie'
shaped bars), each occupying two spaces. An empty space is placed
somewhere on the game board.

  To move, a bar must be beside the empty space, so clicking on
a bar will make it rotate toward the empty space. The bow tie
shaped bars can be placed horizontally, vertically as well as
diagonally. However, the coloured bar can only be placed
horizontally or vertically.

  Complete the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

