@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "TiltOtix" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that TiltOtix runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any bar, if a part of that bar is next to the
empty space, the bar will rotate toward the empty space. Note that
a 'bow tie' shaped bar can be placed in any position, even
diagonally, while the coloured bar can only be placed horizontally
or vertically.

  The goal is simple: move the coloured bar from its starting
position at the top left of the game board, to the lower right
position, indicated by a small square. Try to complete the game
in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

  You can change the colour of the coloured bar by clicking on it,
if the empty space is not located next to the clicked position...

  You can restart the game any time by clicking on the 'New Game'
button.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

